oai_dc:dc.dc:title: The Present and Future Economic Outlook for Beef Production
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Paarlberg, Don
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: During the last 18 months the cattle industry has been buffeted by consumer boycotts, a ban on DES, various phases and stages of price controls, skyrocketing feed grain and protein prices, double digit inflation, and marginal growth in the general economy. Prospects for the next year or two are potentially even more disruptive.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1974; 12-14
